section.section:
Notwithstanding KRS 164A.020, with respect to any educational loan made or financed under this section, and any bonds or notes of the corporation to finance educational loans under this section, as used in KRS 164A.010 to 164A.240, the term:
"Disposable pay" means the amount remaining of a borrower's employment earnings after the deduction of all amounts withheld as required by law;
"Eligible institution" shall be deemed to include any educational institution approved by the corporation;
"Eligible lender" shall be deemed to include any financial institution approved by the corporation; and
"Insured student loan" or "student loan" shall be deemed to include any educational loan.
